BlockOpenHashLong2FloatMap

public BlockOpenHashLong2FloatMap(long size,
                                  int blockshift,
                                  float loadfact,
                                  float growfact,
                                  LongHashingStrategy strategy)
Creates a new hash set.

Parameters:
size - the expected number of elements in the set
blockshift - the base-2 logarithm of the block size (such that the block size is 1<<blockshift)
loadfact - the load factor (between 0 exclusive and 1 inclusive)
growfact - the growth factor (strictly greater than 1)
strategy - the hashing strategy

trim

public boolean trim(long size)
Trims the set table to a given expected number of elements.

This method is generally useful when reusing a set after clearing it, to avoid keeping in memory tables that are significantly smaller than required by the number of elements expected in the set.

Parameters:
size - the expected number of elements in the set
Returns:
true if the operation succeeded
